  "texts": [
    "In a word, improving the robustness of graph pooling methods in the face of dynamic structural changes, noise, outliers, and malicious attacks is an important challenge for current research.",
    "In graph pooling, the aggregation and compression of node information usually involve complex nonlinear transformations, which makes the degree of contribution of node features and subgraphs to the final graph representation unpredictable.",
    "This leads to a lack of transparency as the internal mechanism of the model is like a black box to the user when making predictions or decisions.",
    "In addition, when evaluating the performance of graph pooling methods, evaluation metrics such as accuracy, AUROC, F1 score, etc.",
    "are usually used, and there is a lack of evaluation metrics for interpretability."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}